WEBVTT

00:16.300 --> 00:17.970
{\an1}( <i>bell ringing )</i>

00:22.370 --> 00:24.200
{\an1}( <i>whistle blowing )</i>

00:37.420 --> 00:42.890
{\an1}( <i>playing the blues )</i>

00:57.670 --> 00:59.400
{\an1}( <i>horn honking )</i>

01:03.610 --> 01:04.540
{\an1}D-OHH!

01:04.610 --> 01:05.340
{\an1}( <i>screams )</i>

01:18.990 --> 01:20.230
{\an1}( <i>Homer sighing contentedly )</i>

01:20.290 --> 01:23.160
{\an1}<i>AH, ANOTHER BEAUTIFUL DAY
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIN THE WOMB.</i>

01:23.230 --> 01:26.430
{\an1}( <i>humming "Blue Danube Waltz" )</i>

01:30.570 --> 01:32.470
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

01:35.270 --> 01:38.110
{\an1}<i>LET GO! LET GO!</i>

01:38.180 --> 01:39.780
{\an1}I'M ALL NAKED AND WET!

01:39.850 --> 01:42.220
{\an1}\h\h\h\hGET UP, HOMER.
IT'S TIME FOR CHURCH.

01:42.280 --> 01:43.380
{\an1}I DON'T WANT TO GO.

01:43.450 --> 01:45.120
{\an1}\h\hIT'S CHURCH.
YOU HAVE TO GO.

01:45.180 --> 01:46.450
{\an1}TOO COLD OUT.

01:46.520 --> 01:49.990
{\an1}( <i>growling ferociously )</i>

01:50.060 --> 01:52.270
{\an1}\h\h\h\hI'M TIRED OF HAVING
THIS ARGUMENT EVERY SUNDAY.

01:52.320 --> 01:53.830
{\an1}GET DRESSED.

01:53.890 --> 01:56.560
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOH...
STUPID, ITCHY CHURCH PANTS.

01:56.630 --> 01:58.260
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

01:58.330 --> 02:01.270
{\an1}ONE SIZE FITS ALL, MY BUTT.

02:01.330 --> 02:03.330
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hCOME ON.
WE'RE GOING TO BE LATE.

02:03.400 --> 02:05.270
{\an1}( <i>pants ripping )</i>

02:05.340 --> 02:08.270
{\an1}FORGET IT. I'M NOT GOING.

02:08.970 --> 02:09.970
{\an1}( <i>groans )</i>

02:11.210 --> 02:14.050
{\an1}( <i>squeaking )</i>

02:19.250 --> 02:20.690
{\an1}HEY, WHERE'S HOMER?

02:20.750 --> 02:22.590
{\an1}YOUR FATHER'S... RESTING.

02:22.650 --> 02:25.060
{\an1}RESTING HUNG OVER,
RESTING GOT FIRED?

02:25.120 --> 02:26.460
{\an1}HELP ME OUT HERE.

02:26.530 --> 02:30.170
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAH, I'M JUST
A BIG, TOASTY CINNAMON BUN.

02:30.230 --> 02:33.260
{\an1}I NEVER WANT TO LEAVE THIS BED.

02:33.330 --> 02:36.430
{\an1}UH-OH... GOT TO TAKE A WHIZ.

02:36.500 --> 02:38.600
{\an1}THINK, MAN, THINK.

02:38.670 --> 02:41.210
{\an1}THINK, THINK, THINK.

02:41.270 --> 02:44.440
{\an1}I BETTER GET UP.

02:44.510 --> 02:49.750
{\an1}I'M WHIZZING WITH THE DOOR OPEN,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAND I LOVE IT.

02:50.750 --> 02:57.090
{\an1}♪ WHY, OH, WHY, DELILAH? ♪

02:57.160 --> 03:00.160
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDisk jockey:
It's 11 KBBL degrees below zero.

03:00.230 --> 03:02.430
{\an1}I hope you're someplace warm.

03:02.490 --> 03:04.800
{\an1}YOU BET YOUR SWEET...

03:04.860 --> 03:06.870
{\an1}ASS!

03:10.840 --> 03:12.200
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hMinister:
I'M AFRAID OUR FURNACE

03:12.270 --> 03:13.200
{\an1}ISN'T WORKING.

03:13.270 --> 03:15.970
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMan:
YEAH, WHAT'S THE STORY?

03:16.040 --> 03:18.680
{\an1}BUT LET'S JUST PUT IT
\h\h\hOUT OF OUR MINDS

03:18.740 --> 03:21.710
{\an1}AND TURN TO THE LAMENTATIONS
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hOF JEREMIAH...

03:21.780 --> 03:24.180
{\an1}<i>LONG VERSION.</i>

03:24.250 --> 03:25.920
{\an1}"JOY IS GONE FROM OUR HEARTS.

03:25.980 --> 03:28.850
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hOUR DANCING
HAS TURNED TO MOURNING."

03:35.060 --> 03:35.960
{\an1}( <i>pop-rock music playing )</i>

03:36.030 --> 03:39.100
{\an1}♪ Who wears short shorts? ♪

03:39.160 --> 03:42.000
{\an1}♪ I WEAR SHORT SHORTS. ♪

03:43.570 --> 03:47.270
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hTHE PERFECT CHANCE
TO MAKE MY PATENTED SPACE-AGE

03:47.340 --> 03:50.040
{\an1}OUT-OF-THIS-WORLD MOON WAFFLES.

03:50.110 --> 03:52.040
{\an1}LET'S SEE HERE.

03:52.110 --> 03:53.440
{\an1}CARAMELS...

03:53.510 --> 03:55.350
{\an1}WAFFLE BATTER...

03:55.410 --> 03:57.650
{\an1}LIQUID SMOKE...

03:59.220 --> 04:03.320
{\an1}OOH... WAFFLE RUNOFF.

04:03.390 --> 04:05.190
{\an1}( <i>sizzling )</i>

04:05.260 --> 04:06.860
{\an1}( <i>steam escaping )</i>

04:11.360 --> 04:14.900
{\an1}MMM... FATTENING.

04:14.970 --> 04:18.800
{\an1}\h\h...AND HE WAS CAST INTO
THE FIERY CAULDRON OF HELL.

04:18.870 --> 04:20.339
{\an1}( <i>cracking )</i>

04:20.410 --> 04:22.370
{\an1}THE SEARING HEAT..

04:22.440 --> 04:25.310
{\an1}THE SCALDING RIVERS
\hOF MOLTEN SULPHUR.

04:25.380 --> 04:28.110
{\an1}AHH... I'M THERE.

04:28.180 --> 04:30.320
{\an1}UH-OH.

04:30.380 --> 04:31.780
{\an1}( <i>whistling )</i>

04:31.850 --> 04:33.420
{\an1}HERE, BOY.

04:38.390 --> 04:41.290
{\an1}OKAY, OKAY, OKAY, OKAY!

04:41.360 --> 04:43.330
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hMinister:
THE SERVICE IS ENDED.

04:43.400 --> 04:45.410
{\an1}GO IN PEACE.

04:45.460 --> 04:47.170
{\an1}( <i>organ playing )</i>

04:47.230 --> 04:48.930
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

04:49.000 --> 04:52.570
{\an1}THE DOOR'S FROZEN SHUT...
AND IT'S THE ONLY WAY OUT!

04:52.640 --> 04:53.640
{\an1}( <i>mumbling )</i>

04:53.710 --> 04:56.010
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hOUR FATHER
WHO ART IN HEAVEN...

04:56.070 --> 04:57.840
{\an1}\h\h\hLISA, THIS IS
NEITHER THE TIME
\h\hNOR THE PLACE.

04:57.910 --> 04:59.910
{\an1}Disk Jockey 1:
That was Johnny Calhoun with..

04:59.980 --> 05:02.110
{\an1}"Gonna Find Me a Genie
\hWith a Magic Bikini"

05:02.180 --> 05:04.450
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDisk Jockey 2:
...Johnny Calhoun's next record
\h\h\h\hwas a spoken-word album

05:04.520 --> 05:05.720
{\an1}of his right-wing
\hpolitical views.

05:05.780 --> 05:07.050
{\an1}It kinda killed his career.

05:07.120 --> 05:08.450
{\an1}\h\hIf you can tell me
the name of that album

05:08.520 --> 05:09.450
{\an1}call our contest line now.

05:09.520 --> 05:11.320
{\an1}I KNOW THAT!

05:17.160 --> 05:19.230
{\an1}HELLO, THIS IS HOMER SIMPSON.

05:19.300 --> 05:21.230
{\an1}Homer, can you name that title?

05:21.300 --> 05:24.770
{\an1}<i>THIS THINGS I BELIEVE.</i>

05:24.840 --> 05:27.040
{\an1}\h\hCan we accept that?
( <i>cash register jingling )</i>

05:27.110 --> 05:27.940
{\an1}WHOO-HOO!

05:30.610 --> 05:31.940
{\an1}HOW'S THAT DOOR COMING,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWILLIE?

05:32.010 --> 05:34.650
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMIRACLES ARE
YOUR DEPARTMENT, REVEREND.

05:34.710 --> 05:37.220
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hMinister:
WHILE WE'RE WAITING,
\h\hWHY DON'T I READ

05:37.280 --> 05:39.180
{\an1}FROM THE SUNDAY BULLETIN?

05:39.250 --> 05:40.550
{\an1}"CARD TABLE FOR SALE.

05:40.620 --> 05:43.520
{\an1}\h\h\h\h"TOP BADLY DAMAGED,
LEG MISSING, OTHERWISE FINE.

05:43.590 --> 05:45.720
{\an1}ONE DOLLAR OR BEST OFFER."

05:45.790 --> 05:48.960
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hWoman:
\h\hYou must be the three
chiropractors I sent for.

05:49.030 --> 05:51.200
{\an1}Now, start manipulating
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hmy spine.

05:51.260 --> 05:54.570
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMan:
Hey, Moe, we don't know nothing
\h\h\h\h\h\habout manipulating.

05:54.630 --> 05:57.100
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMoe:
Grab her spine and get cracking.

05:57.170 --> 05:59.300
{\an1}MOE IS THEIR LEADER.

05:59.370 --> 06:01.010
{\an1}( <i>bone cracking )</i>

06:03.110 --> 06:04.110
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

06:04.180 --> 06:05.010
{\an1}HUZZAH!

06:06.780 --> 06:09.480
{\an1}\h\h\h\hPLEASE, PLEASE,
CHRISTIANS, DON'T PUSH.

06:09.550 --> 06:10.950
{\an1}\h\h\hEXCUSE ME.
PARDON ME.WHOA!

06:11.020 --> 06:12.980
{\an1}\hCOMING THROUGH.
LOVE THAT HAT, BABY.

06:13.050 --> 06:18.320
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hCOME ON, TV, GIVE ME
SOME OF THAT SWEET, SWEET PEP.

06:18.390 --> 06:19.420
{\an1}Let's define our terms,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hgentlemen.

06:19.490 --> 06:20.990
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hAre we talking
about redistricting

06:21.060 --> 06:23.130
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hor are we talking
about reapportionment?

06:23.190 --> 06:25.100
{\an1}OH, WELL. CAN'T WIN THEM ALL.

06:25.160 --> 06:29.270
{\an1}\h\hWe interrupt this program
to bring you a football game.

06:29.330 --> 06:31.270
{\an1}YES!

06:33.470 --> 06:35.840
{\an1}( <i>engine sputtering )</i>

06:35.910 --> 06:39.280
{\an1}( <i>sputtering )</i>

06:39.340 --> 06:40.110
{\an1}( <i>Marge mimicking
engine sputtering )</i>

06:40.180 --> 06:41.680
{\an1}GIVE IT A LITTLE MORE GAS.

06:41.750 --> 06:43.580
{\an1}NO, NO, THAT'S TOO MUCH.

06:43.650 --> 06:45.550
{\an1}KNOW WHAT I THINK
\h\h\hWOULD HELP?

06:45.620 --> 06:47.750
{\an1}WHAT?! WHAT WOULD HELP?!

06:47.820 --> 06:49.490
{\an1}NOTHING.

06:49.550 --> 06:53.620
{\an1}\h\h\h\hGame announcer:
A 98-yard triple reverse
ties the score at 63-63.

06:53.690 --> 06:56.730
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hWe have seen nothing
but razzle-dazzle here today.

06:56.800 --> 06:59.470
{\an1}Three visits from Morgana,
\h\h\h\hthe Kissing Bandit

06:59.530 --> 07:02.000
{\an1}and the astonishing return
\h\h\h\h\h\hof Jim Brown.

07:02.070 --> 07:03.500
{\an1}WHOO-HOO!

07:03.570 --> 07:06.470
{\an1}IS THAT WHAT I THINK IT IS?

07:10.110 --> 07:12.110
{\an1}MM-HMM.

07:12.180 --> 07:15.680
{\an1}I FOUND A PENNY!

07:15.750 --> 07:18.520
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hCOULD THIS BE
THE BEST DAY OF MY LIFE?

07:21.750 --> 07:23.520
{\an1}\h( <i>laughing
hysterically )</i>

07:26.220 --> 07:27.860
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLOOKS LIKE
WE HAVE A NEW CHAMPION.

07:29.290 --> 07:31.830
{\an1}AH, MY BELOVED FAMILY.

07:31.900 --> 07:33.300
{\an1}HOW WAS CHURCH?

07:33.370 --> 07:36.310
{\an1}( <i>grumbling heatedly )</i>

07:36.370 --> 07:39.040
{\an1}\h\h\hI HAVE BEEN HAVING
THE BEST DAY OF MY LIFE

07:39.100 --> 07:41.640
{\an1}\h\hAND I OWE IT ALL
TO SKIPPING CHURCH.

07:41.710 --> 07:43.670
{\an1}THAT'S A TERRIBLE THING TO SAY.

07:43.740 --> 07:45.540
{\an1}\h\h\hYOUR FATHER
DOESN'T MEAN THAT.

07:45.610 --> 07:47.040
{\an1}LIKE FUN, I DON'T.

07:47.110 --> 07:50.050
{\an1}MARGE, I'M NEVER GOING
\h\h\hTO CHURCH AGAIN.

07:50.120 --> 07:53.730
{\an1}HOMER, ARE YOU ACTUALLY
\hGIVING UP YOUR FAITH?

07:53.790 --> 07:56.830
{\an1}NO! NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

07:56.890 --> 08:02.060
{\an1}WELL, YES.

08:02.130 --> 08:04.760
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE GIVING UP CHURCH, HOMER.

08:04.830 --> 08:06.200
{\an1}HEY, WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL

08:06.260 --> 08:08.500
{\an1}ABOUT GOING TO SOME BUILDING
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hEVERY SUNDAY?

08:08.570 --> 08:09.870
{\an1}I MEAN, ISN'T GOD
\h\h\h\h\h\hEVERYWHERE?

08:09.930 --> 08:11.170
{\an1}AMEN, BROTHER.

08:11.240 --> 08:12.440
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hAND DON'T
YOU THINK THAT
\h\hTHE ALMIGHTY

08:12.500 --> 08:13.940
{\an1}HAS BETTER THINGS
\h\hTO WORRY ABOUT

08:14.010 --> 08:15.240
{\an1}THAN WHERE ONE LITTLE GUY

08:15.310 --> 08:17.440
{\an1}SPENDS ONE HOUR
\h\hOF HIS WEEK?

08:17.510 --> 08:18.210
{\an1}TELL IT, DADDY.

08:18.280 --> 08:19.040
{\an1}AND WHAT IF WE PICKED

08:19.110 --> 08:20.510
{\an1}THE WRONG RELIGION?

08:20.580 --> 08:22.910
{\an1}\h\h\h\hEVERY WEEK WE'RE JUST
MAKING GOD MADDER AND MADDER.

08:22.980 --> 08:25.350
{\an1}TESTIFY!

08:26.750 --> 08:27.850
{\an1}( <i>growls )</i>

08:27.920 --> 08:30.350
{\an1}\h\h\hLORD, MY HUSBAND
IS BY NO MEANS PERFECT

08:30.420 --> 08:32.419
{\an1}BUT HE'S A KIND, DECENT MAN.

08:32.490 --> 08:35.090
{\an1}\h\h\hPLEASE SHOW HIM
THE ERROR OF HIS WAYS.

08:35.159 --> 08:37.059
{\an1}MARGE, COME TO BED.

08:37.130 --> 08:39.260
{\an1}NO, HOMER.

08:39.330 --> 08:42.030
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hHE DOESN'T MEAN
TO BE SACRILEGIOUS, LORD.

08:42.100 --> 08:44.570
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hHE JUST LIKES
TO SLEEP IN ON SUNDAYS.

08:44.640 --> 08:45.840
{\an1}MARGE...

08:45.900 --> 08:49.110
{\an1}COME TO BED,
\h\h\hMARGE.

08:49.170 --> 08:51.780
{\an1}LORD, HE'S NOT A BAD PERSON,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hLORD, REALLY.

08:51.840 --> 08:53.180
{\an1}HE JUST SOMETIMES...

08:53.240 --> 08:54.880
{\an1}IT'S GOOD FOR WHAT AILS YOU.

08:54.950 --> 08:57.520
{\an1}HE DOESN'T MEAN ANY HARM.

08:57.580 --> 08:59.880
{\an1}I CAN WAIT ALL...

08:59.950 --> 09:01.190
{\an1}( <i>snoring )</i>

09:10.300 --> 09:11.940
{\an1}OOH!

09:22.470 --> 09:23.640
{\an1}GOD?

09:23.710 --> 09:27.140
{\an1}<i>THOU HAST FORSAKEN MY CHURCH!</i>

09:27.210 --> 09:29.380
{\an1}WELL, KIND OF...
\h\h\h\h\hBUT...

09:29.450 --> 09:30.750
{\an1}<i>BUT WHAT?</i>

09:30.820 --> 09:32.380
{\an1}I'M NOT A BAD GUY.

09:32.450 --> 09:34.690
{\an1}\h\h\hI WORK HARD
AND I LOVE MY KIDS

09:34.750 --> 09:36.690
{\an1}SO WHY SHOULD I SPEND
\h\h\h\hHALF MY SUNDAY

09:36.760 --> 09:38.930
{\an1}\h\h\h\hHEARING ABOUT
HOW I'M GOING TO HELL?

09:38.990 --> 09:40.890
{\an1}<i>HMM.</i>

09:40.960 --> 09:42.990
{\an1}<i>YOU'VE GOT A POINT THERE.</i>

09:43.060 --> 09:44.230
{\an1}<i>YOU KNOW, SOMETIMES</i>

09:44.300 --> 09:46.760
{\an1}\h\h\h\h <i>EVEN I'D RATHER
BE WATCHING FOOTBALL.</i>

09:46.830 --> 09:49.370
{\an1}\h\h <i>DOES ST. LOUIS
STILL HAVE A TEAM?</i>

09:49.430 --> 09:50.900
{\an1}NO. THEY MOVED
\hTO PHOENIX.

09:50.970 --> 09:52.170
{\an1}<i>OH, YEAH.</i>

09:52.240 --> 09:55.140
{\an1}YOU KNOW WHAT I REALLY HATE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hABOUT CHURCH?

09:55.210 --> 09:56.870
{\an1}THOSE <i>BORING SERMONS.</i>

09:56.940 --> 09:57.780
{\an1}( <i>God sighing )</i>

09:57.840 --> 09:59.210
{\an1}<i>I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.</i>

09:59.280 --> 10:02.010
{\an1}<i>THAT REVEREND LOVEJOY
REALLY DISPLEASES ME.</i>

10:02.080 --> 10:04.650
{\an1}<i>I THINK I'LL GIVE HIM
\h\h\h\h\hA CANKER SORE.</i>

10:04.720 --> 10:05.880
{\an1}GIVE HIM ONE FOR ME.

10:05.950 --> 10:07.180
{\an1}<i>I WILL.</i>

10:07.250 --> 10:10.320
{\an1}\hSO I FIGURE I SHOULD
JUST TRY TO LIVE RIGHT

10:10.390 --> 10:12.590
{\an1}AND WORSHIP YOU
\hIN MY OWN WAY.

10:12.660 --> 10:14.330
{\an1}<i>HOMER, IT'S A DEAL.</i>

10:14.390 --> 10:16.190
{\an1}<i>NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME</i>

10:16.260 --> 10:20.060
{\an1}<i>I HAVE TO APPEAR IN A TORTILLA
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIN MEXICO.</i>

10:28.010 --> 10:29.610
{\an1}DAD, CAN I ASK YOU
\h\h\hA QUESTION?

10:29.670 --> 10:30.840
{\an1}SURE, HONEY.

10:30.910 --> 10:33.780
{\an1}\hWHY ARE YOU DEDICATING
YOUR LIFE TO BLASPHEMY?

10:33.850 --> 10:35.220
{\an1}DON'T WORRY,
SWEETHEART.

10:35.280 --> 10:38.320
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIF I'M WRONG,
I'LL RECANT ON MY DEATHBED.

10:38.380 --> 10:41.620
{\an1}HELLO, MY ANIMAL FRIENDS.

10:41.690 --> 10:43.190
{\an1}PEACE BE WITH YOU.

10:45.190 --> 10:47.120
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGUYS, PLEASE,
COULD YOU GIVE ME FIVE MINUTES?

10:47.190 --> 10:48.960
{\an1}REVEREND LOVEJOY

10:49.030 --> 10:50.230
{\an1}I HAD AN ULTERIOR MOTIVE

10:50.300 --> 10:52.040
{\an1}IN INVITING YOU TO DINNER.

10:52.100 --> 10:53.030
{\an1}WHAT?!

10:53.100 --> 10:54.770
{\an1}NO, IT'S NOTHING BAD.

10:54.830 --> 10:56.330
{\an1}I'M JUST CONCERNED
BECAUSE MY HUSBAND

10:56.400 --> 10:58.740
{\an1}HASN'T BEEN ATTENDING
YOUR SERVICES LATELY.

10:58.800 --> 11:01.240
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hI WASN'T SURE
I WAS DOING THE RIGHT THING

11:01.310 --> 11:04.410
{\an1}\hBUT GOD HIMSELF TOLD ME
I SHOULD SEEK A NEW PATH.

11:04.480 --> 11:05.580
{\an1}OH, REALLY?

11:05.640 --> 11:07.950
{\an1}YEAH. HE APPEARED BEFORE ME
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hIN A DREAM

11:08.010 --> 11:09.210
{\an1}AND I KNEW THAT WAS SPECIAL

11:09.280 --> 11:12.150
{\an1}'CAUSE I USUALLY DREAM
ABOUT NAKED... MARGE.

11:12.220 --> 11:13.180
{\an1}( <i>growls )</i>

11:13.250 --> 11:15.220
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSO, HOMER,
YOU SAW THE BIG CHEESE?

11:15.290 --> 11:16.890
{\an1}WHAT DID HE
\hLOOK LIKE?

11:16.960 --> 11:18.400
{\an1}PERFECT TEETH,
NICE SMELL...

11:18.460 --> 11:19.960
{\an1}A CLASS ACT
ALL THE WAY.

11:20.020 --> 11:22.030
{\an1}HOMER, YOU'RE CRAZY!

11:22.090 --> 11:24.130
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hTELL HIM
THIS IS ALL CRAZY.

11:24.200 --> 11:27.700
{\an1}\h\h\hHOMER, I'D LIKE YOU
TO REMEMBER MATTHEW 7:26--

11:27.770 --> 11:28.970
{\an1}THE FOOLISH MAN

11:29.030 --> 11:30.940
{\an1}WHO BUILT HIS HOUSE
\h\h\h\h\h\hON SAND.

11:31.000 --> 11:33.840
{\an1}AND YOU REMEMBER...

11:33.910 --> 11:37.250
{\an1}MATTHEW... 21:17.

11:37.310 --> 11:38.410
{\an1}"AND HE LEFT THEM

11:38.480 --> 11:40.750
{\an1}"AND WENT OUT OF THE CITY
\h\h\h\h\h\h\hINTO BETHANY

11:40.810 --> 11:41.910
{\an1}AND HE LODGED THERE"?

11:41.980 --> 11:43.880
{\an1}YEAH.

11:43.950 --> 11:45.720
{\an1}THINK ABOUT IT.

11:45.780 --> 11:46.950
{\an1}HELLO, WORK?

11:47.020 --> 11:48.050
{\an1}THIS IS HOMER SIMPSON.

11:48.120 --> 11:50.120
{\an1}I WON'T BE COMING IN TOMORROW.

11:50.190 --> 11:51.760
{\an1}RELIGIOUS HOLIDAY.

11:51.820 --> 11:52.890
{\an1}THE FEAST OF...

11:52.960 --> 11:54.930
{\an1}MAXIMUM OCCUPANCY.

11:54.990 --> 11:56.330
{\an1}PRETTY SLICK.

11:56.390 --> 11:58.630
{\an1}\hYOU SHOULD JOIN
MY RELIGION, MOE.

11:58.700 --> 11:59.630
{\an1}IT'S GREAT.

11:59.700 --> 12:00.830
{\an1}NO HELL, NO KNEELING...

12:00.900 --> 12:02.270
{\an1}SORRY, HOMER.

12:02.330 --> 12:05.100
{\an1}I WAS BORN A SNAKE HANDLER
\h\h\h\hAND I'LL DIE ONE.

12:05.170 --> 12:06.540
{\an1}( <i>doorbell rings )</i>

12:07.670 --> 12:09.770
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hNEIGHBOR,
I HEARD ABOUT YOUR HERESY

12:09.840 --> 12:13.510
{\an1}AND WE'VE MADE IT OUR MISSION
TO WIN YOU BACK TO THE FLOCK.

12:13.580 --> 12:14.580
{\an1}NO SALE.

12:14.650 --> 12:15.880
{\an1}HOMER, CHRISTIAN LIFE

12:15.950 --> 12:17.950
{\an1}ISN'T ALL PRAYING AND SACRIFICE.

12:18.020 --> 12:19.920
{\an1}HEY, DIG THIS.

12:19.980 --> 12:21.390
{\an1}♪ GOD SAID TO NOAH ♪

12:21.450 --> 12:23.220
{\an1}\h♪ THERE'S GONNA BE
A FLOODY-FLOODY... ♪

12:24.390 --> 12:25.320
{\an1}( <i>snoring )</i>

12:25.390 --> 12:26.690
{\an1}( <i>phone rings )</i>

12:26.760 --> 12:28.330
{\an1}♪ Rain came down ♪

12:28.390 --> 12:31.100
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h♪ It started
to get muddy-muddy... ♪

12:35.030 --> 12:37.000
{\an1}♪ GET THOSE ANIMALS ♪

12:37.070 --> 12:39.140
{\an1}♪ OUT ON THE ARKY-ARKY... ♪

12:39.200 --> 12:40.540
{\an1}LEAVE ME ALONE.

12:40.610 --> 12:42.980
{\an1}DAD, THE HEATHEN'S
\h\hGETTING AWAY.

12:43.040 --> 12:44.480
{\an1}I SEE HIM, SON.

12:48.150 --> 12:50.080
{\an1}( <i>clanging )</i>

12:51.520 --> 12:52.520
{\an1}( <i>horn blaring )</i>

13:08.370 --> 13:09.270
{\an1}( <i>yells )</i>

13:12.370 --> 13:14.210
{\an1}( <i>laughs )</i>

13:14.270 --> 13:15.210
{\an1}( <i>squeaking )</i>

13:15.270 --> 13:16.770
{\an1}WHERE ARE WE GOING?

13:16.840 --> 13:17.710
{\an1}GARBAGE ISLAND.

13:18.940 --> 13:19.940
{\an1}( <i>foghorn blasts )</i>

13:25.850 --> 13:28.190
{\an1}( <i>fishing reel ticking sound )</i>

13:36.330 --> 13:37.560
{\an1}( <i>ticking )</i>

13:43.300 --> 13:44.340
{\an1}( <i>ticking )</i>

13:44.400 --> 13:45.270
{\an1}HUH?

13:47.910 --> 13:49.070
{\an1}( <i>screaming )</i>

13:54.580 --> 13:57.050
{\an1}( <i>cheering )</i>

13:57.120 --> 13:58.890
{\an1}( <i>laughing )</i>

13:58.950 --> 13:59.880
{\an1}LET'S GO, KIDS.

13:59.950 --> 14:02.150
{\an1}HOW COME WE HAVE
TO GO TO CHURCH

14:02.220 --> 14:03.790
{\an1}\h\h\hAND DAD GETS
TO WATCH CARTOONS?

14:03.860 --> 14:05.730
{\an1}( <i>growls )</i>

14:05.790 --> 14:06.920
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hI HAVE
A RESPONSIBILITY

14:06.990 --> 14:08.930
{\an1}TO RAISE THESE
CHILDREN RIGHT

14:08.990 --> 14:09.990
{\an1}AND UNLESS
YOU CHANGE

14:10.060 --> 14:11.830
{\an1}I'LL HAVE TO TELL THEM

14:11.900 --> 14:12.960
{\an1}THEIR FATHER IS...

14:13.030 --> 14:13.930
{\an1}WELL, WICKED.

14:14.000 --> 14:15.430
{\an1}KIDS, LET ME TELL YOU

14:15.500 --> 14:17.900
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hABOUT ANOTHER
SO-CALLED "WICKED" GUY.

14:17.970 --> 14:20.970
{\an1}\h\hHE HAD LONG HAIR
AND SOME WILD IDEAS

14:21.040 --> 14:22.410
{\an1}AND HE DIDN'T ALWAYS DO

14:22.470 --> 14:24.980
{\an1}WHAT OTHER PEOPLE
THOUGHT WAS RIGHT

14:25.040 --> 14:28.150
{\an1}AND THAT MAN'S NAME WAS...

14:28.210 --> 14:29.680
{\an1}I FORGET.

14:29.750 --> 14:30.880
{\an1}BUT THE POINT IS...

14:30.950 --> 14:32.120
{\an1}I FORGET THAT TOO.

14:32.180 --> 14:34.890
{\an1}\h\h\hMARGE, YOU KNOW
WHO I'M TALKING ABOUT.

14:34.950 --> 14:36.950
{\an1}HE USED TO DRIVE
\hTHAT BLUE CAR.

14:37.020 --> 14:38.960
{\an1}KIDS, COULD YOU WAIT OUTSIDE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hFOR US?

14:39.990 --> 14:41.360
{\an1}\h\h\hHOMER, PLEASE
DON'T MAKE ME CHOOSE

14:41.430 --> 14:43.330
{\an1}BETWEEN MY MAN AND MY GOD

14:43.390 --> 14:45.630
{\an1}BECAUSE YOU JUST CAN'T WIN.

14:45.700 --> 14:46.960
{\an1}THERE YOU GO AGAIN.

14:47.030 --> 14:49.400
{\an1}\h\h\hALWAYS TAKING
SOMEONE ELSE'S SIDE.

14:49.470 --> 14:52.940
{\an1}FLANDERS, THE WATER DEPARTMENT,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGOD...

14:53.000 --> 14:54.710
{\an1}I'M ONLY GOING
\h\hTO ASK YOU

14:54.770 --> 14:56.010
{\an1}ONE LAST TIME.

14:56.070 --> 14:59.010
{\an1}\hARE YOU SURE YOU WON'T
COME WITH US TO CHURCH?

14:59.080 --> 15:01.350
{\an1}\h\h\hComing up next:
make your own ladder.

15:01.410 --> 15:02.310
{\an1}VERY SURE.

15:05.420 --> 15:07.250
{\an1}Lovejoy:
<i>MY FRIENDS</i>

15:07.320 --> 15:10.150
{\an1}THE DEVIL WALKS AMONG US.

15:10.220 --> 15:11.890
{\an1}( <i>gasping )</i>

15:11.960 --> 15:13.260
{\an1}I GOT HIM!

15:13.320 --> 15:16.430
{\an1}NO, DON'T LOOK FOR THE PITCHFORK
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hAND POINTY TAIL.

15:16.490 --> 15:19.260
{\an1}TODAY'S DEVIL HAS ASSUMED
\h\hA MORE SEDUCTIVE FORM

15:19.330 --> 15:20.800
{\an1}PLEASING TO THE EYE.

15:20.870 --> 15:22.380
{\an1}OH-H-H.

15:22.430 --> 15:24.900
{\an1}\h\h\h\hAN INTERVIEW
WITH LORNE MICHAELS.

15:24.970 --> 15:25.900
{\an1}OH-H-H-H.

15:25.970 --> 15:27.970
{\an1}WAIT, THAT'S NO GOOD.

15:28.040 --> 15:29.740
{\an1}HEY, NOW WE'RE TALKING.

15:29.810 --> 15:32.810
{\an1}"OUR UNABASHED DICTIONARY
\h\h\h\h\h\hDEFINES I.U.D.

15:32.880 --> 15:35.710
{\an1}AS 'LOVE SPRINGS INTERNAL.'"

15:35.780 --> 15:36.810
{\an1}( <i>laughs )</i>

15:36.880 --> 15:38.180
{\an1}I DON'T GET IT.

15:38.250 --> 15:39.250
{\an1}( <i>doorbell rings )</i>

15:39.320 --> 15:41.690
{\an1}\h\h\h\hHELLO.
I'M COLLECTING

15:41.750 --> 15:44.120
{\an1}FOR THE BROTHERHOOD
\hOF JEWISH CLOWNS.

15:44.190 --> 15:46.720
{\an1}LAST YEAR TORNADOS
CLAIMED THE LIVES

15:46.790 --> 15:48.890
{\an1}OF 75 JEWISH CLOWNS.

15:48.960 --> 15:50.160
{\an1}THE WORST INCIDENT

15:50.230 --> 15:52.830
{\an1}WAS DURING OUR CONVENTION
\h\h\h\hIN LUBBOCK, TEXAS.

15:52.900 --> 15:56.530
{\an1}\h\hTHERE WERE FLOPPY SHOES
AND RAINBOW WIGS EVERYWHERE.

15:56.600 --> 15:58.800
{\an1}IT WAS TERRIBLE.

15:58.870 --> 15:59.900
{\an1}WAIT A MINUTE.

15:59.970 --> 16:02.240
{\an1}IS THIS A RELIGIOUS THING?

16:02.310 --> 16:04.270
{\an1}\h\h\hA RELIGIOUS
CLOWN THING, YES.

16:04.340 --> 16:05.110
{\an1}SORRY.

16:05.180 --> 16:06.340
{\an1}WELL, BLESS YOU ANY...

16:06.410 --> 16:09.910
{\an1}REMEMBER THE SABBATH DAY
\h\h\h\hTO KEEP IT HOLY.

16:11.480 --> 16:13.850
{\an1}APU, I SEE YOU'RE NOT IN CHURCH.

16:13.920 --> 16:14.950
{\an1}OH, BUT I AM.

16:15.020 --> 16:16.720
{\an1}I HAVE A SHRINE TO GANESHA

16:16.790 --> 16:19.390
{\an1}THE GOD OF WORLDLY WISDOM,
\hIN THE EMPLOYEE LOUNGE.

16:19.460 --> 16:21.230
{\an1}HEY, GANESHA,
WANT A PEANUT?

16:21.290 --> 16:23.130
{\an1}DO NOT OFFER MY GOD A PEANUT.

16:23.190 --> 16:25.300
{\an1}\h\h\h\hWHEN THEY WERE
HANDING OUT RELIGIONS

16:25.360 --> 16:27.460
{\an1}YOU MUST HAVE BEEN
\h\hTAKING A WHIZ.

16:27.530 --> 16:29.800
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hMR. SIMPSON,
PLEASE PAY FOR YOUR PURCHASES

16:29.870 --> 16:31.170
{\an1}GET OUT, AND COME AGAIN.

16:31.240 --> 16:34.610
{\an1}PRIDE GOETH BEFORE DESTRUCTION.

16:34.670 --> 16:36.010
{\an1}BOY...

16:36.070 --> 16:40.310
{\an1}EVERYONE IS STUPID EXCEPT ME.

16:40.380 --> 16:42.110
{\an1}( <i>snoring )</i>

16:54.190 --> 16:55.330
{\an1}( <i>explosion )</i>

16:56.960 --> 17:00.860
{\an1}MARGE, TURN DOWN THE HEAT.

17:00.930 --> 17:03.000
{\an1}THAT'S BETTER.

17:07.240 --> 17:08.540
{\an1}( <i>snoring )</i>

17:13.950 --> 17:14.819
{\an1}( <i>growling )</i>

17:24.619 --> 17:25.960
{\an1}AH! FIRE!

17:26.020 --> 17:28.359
{\an1}WHAT DO I DO?!
WHAT DO I DO?!

17:28.430 --> 17:29.490
{\an1}( <i>coughing )</i>

17:29.560 --> 17:30.990
{\an1}OH, THE SONG, THE SONG.

17:31.060 --> 17:33.230
{\an1}♪ WHEN A FIRE STARTS TO BURN ♪

17:33.300 --> 17:35.070
{\an1}♪ THERE'S A LESSON
\hYOU MUST LEARN ♪

17:35.130 --> 17:37.200
{\an1}♪ SOMETHING, SOMETHING,
\h\h\hTHEN YOU'LL SEE ♪

17:37.270 --> 17:39.640
{\an1}♪ YOU'LL AVOID CATASTROPHE. ♪

17:39.700 --> 17:41.370
{\an1}D-OHHH!

17:41.440 --> 17:43.970
{\an1}( <i>coughing )</i>

17:44.040 --> 17:44.980
{\an1}( <i>Apu gasps )</i>

17:45.040 --> 17:46.780
{\an1}FIRE AT THE SIMPSON PLACE!

17:49.410 --> 17:50.480
{\an1}YOU'RE ON YOUR HONOR

17:50.550 --> 17:51.450
{\an1}NOT TO STEAL ANYTHING.

17:51.520 --> 17:53.920
{\an1}OH, WE WON'T.

17:55.520 --> 17:56.950
{\an1}LITTLE JUMPSHID

17:57.020 --> 17:58.620
{\an1}\h\h\h\hTHE STORE
IS IN YOUR HANDS.

17:58.690 --> 18:00.420
{\an1}HOW I HAVE WAITED

18:00.490 --> 18:02.530
{\an1}FOR THIS DAY.

18:12.000 --> 18:13.570
{\an1}( <i>quacking )</i>

18:17.280 --> 18:20.620
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hYOU DUCKS
ARE REALLY TRYING MY PATIENCE

18:20.680 --> 18:22.210
{\an1}BUT YOU'RE SO CUTE.

18:23.550 --> 18:26.220
{\an1}HOMER! HOMER!

18:34.390 --> 18:37.690
{\an1}NOOO!

18:48.770 --> 18:53.580
{\an1}DEAR LORD, MAY YOUR LOVING HAND
\h\hGUIDE HOMER TO THE MATTRESS,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hSQUARE AND TRUE.

18:58.480 --> 19:00.720
{\an1}OKAY.

19:06.720 --> 19:08.830
{\an1}( <i>sirens wailing )</i>

19:08.890 --> 19:10.560
{\an1}( <i>coughing )</i>

19:10.630 --> 19:13.530
{\an1}FLANDERS, YOU SAVED ME.

19:13.600 --> 19:14.900
{\an1}WHY?

19:14.970 --> 19:19.300
{\an1}HECK, YOU WOULD HAVE DONE
\h\h\h\h\hTHE SAME FOR ME.

19:19.370 --> 19:21.440
{\an1}<i>HELP! HELP!</i>

19:21.510 --> 19:23.010
{\an1}( <i>laughing )</i>

19:24.510 --> 19:26.410
{\an1}THAT'S RIGHT, OLD FRIEND.

19:26.480 --> 19:27.610
{\an1}DAD!
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hDAD!

19:27.680 --> 19:28.980
{\an1}HOMIE, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

19:29.050 --> 19:32.620
{\an1}OUR MAGAZINES AND ROACH TRAPS,
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGONE!

19:32.680 --> 19:34.520
{\an1}ALL GONE.

19:34.590 --> 19:36.450
{\an1}( <i>cat howling )</i>

19:36.520 --> 19:39.720
{\an1}I SAVED YOUR CAT.

19:39.790 --> 19:41.690
{\an1}OW! THAT HURT.

19:41.760 --> 19:45.100
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\hHEY, WHAT
ARE THESE AXES FOR?

19:45.160 --> 19:46.160
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW.

19:46.230 --> 19:47.260
{\an1}CHOPPING STUFF.

19:47.330 --> 19:48.770
{\an1}GOTCHA!

19:48.830 --> 19:51.130
{\an1}( <i>grunting )</i>

19:51.200 --> 19:52.470
{\an1}SOME NICE CHOPPING.

19:52.540 --> 19:55.670
{\an1}TRULY, THIS WAS
\hAN ACT OF GOD.

19:57.170 --> 19:58.310
{\an1}HEY, WAIT A MINUTE!

19:58.380 --> 20:00.740
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\hFLANDERS IS
A REGULAR CHARLIE CHURCH

20:00.810 --> 20:03.050
{\an1}AND GOD DIDN'T SAVE HIS HOUSE.

20:05.550 --> 20:06.650
{\an1}D-OHHH!

20:06.720 --> 20:09.320
{\an1}ANY VALUABLES
IN THE HOUSE?

20:09.390 --> 20:10.650
{\an1}WELL, THE PICASSO

20:10.720 --> 20:13.690
{\an1}\h\hMY COLLECTION
OF CLASSIC CARS...

20:13.760 --> 20:16.230
{\an1}THIS POLICY ONLY COVERS
\h\h\h\h\hACTUAL LOSSES

20:16.290 --> 20:17.430
{\an1}NOT MADE-UP STUFF.

20:17.500 --> 20:19.240
{\an1}WELL, THAT'S JUST GREAT.

20:19.300 --> 20:21.770
{\an1}FIRE-- MAN'S OLDEST FOE.

20:21.830 --> 20:24.770
{\an1}INSATIABLE, REMORSELESS,
\h\h\h\h\hUNQUENCHABLE.

20:24.840 --> 20:26.070
{\an1}\h\h\hFireman:
HEY, IT'S OUT.

20:26.140 --> 20:27.570
{\an1}YAY!

20:27.640 --> 20:28.570
{\an1}COMING UP NEXT:

20:28.640 --> 20:29.770
{\an1}WHICH WORK BETTER--

20:29.840 --> 20:32.740
{\an1}SPRINGY CLOTHESPINS
\hOR THE OTHER KIND?

20:36.410 --> 20:39.750
{\an1}YOU KNOW, I HAVE A FEELING
\h\hTHERE'S A LESSON HERE.

20:39.820 --> 20:41.520
{\an1}YES. THE LESSON IS...

20:41.590 --> 20:42.550
{\an1}NO, DON'T TELL ME.

20:42.620 --> 20:43.750
{\an1}I'LL GET IT.

20:43.820 --> 20:45.290
{\an1}OH, I KNOW.

20:45.360 --> 20:47.460
{\an1}THE LORD IS VENGEFUL.

20:47.530 --> 20:48.770
{\an1}OH, SPITEFUL ONE

20:48.830 --> 20:51.730
{\an1}\h\h\hSHOW ME WHO TO SMITE
AND THEY SHALL BE SMOTEN.

20:51.800 --> 20:54.560
{\an1}GOD DIDN'T SET YOUR HOUSE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hON FIRE.

20:54.630 --> 20:56.800
{\an1}NO, BUT HE WAS WORKING
\h\h\h\hIN THE HEARTS

20:56.870 --> 20:59.870
{\an1}\h\h\h\hOF YOUR NEIGHBORS
WHEN THEY WENT TO YOUR AID

20:59.940 --> 21:01.000
{\an1}BE THEY CHRISTIAN

21:01.070 --> 21:02.010
{\an1}JEW, OR...

21:02.070 --> 21:03.610
{\an1}MISCELLANEOUS.

21:03.670 --> 21:06.080
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hHINDU.
THERE ARE 700 MILLION OF US.

21:06.140 --> 21:07.340
{\an1}AW, THAT'S SUPER.

21:07.410 --> 21:09.380
{\an1}I WAS RUDE TO ALL OF YOU

21:09.450 --> 21:10.710
{\an1}AND YOU SAVED MY LIFE

21:10.780 --> 21:13.080
{\an1}WHEN YOU COULD HAVE
\h\h\hLEFT ME TO FRY

21:13.150 --> 21:15.820
{\an1}LIKE THE PROVERBIAL PANCAKE
\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hTHAT I AM.

21:15.890 --> 21:20.190
{\an1}OH, HOMIE, I'M SO GLAD
TO HEAR YOU SAY THAT.

21:20.260 --> 21:22.360
{\an1}WOULD YOU GIVE CHURCH
\h\h\h\h\hANOTHER TRY?

21:22.430 --> 21:25.800
{\an1}I'LL BE THERE NEXT SUNDAY,
\h\h\h\hFRONT ROW CENTER.

21:25.860 --> 21:28.930
{\an1}( <i>snoring )</i>

21:34.310 --> 21:35.780
{\an1}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hGod:
<i>DON'T FEEL BAD, HOMER.</i>

21:35.840 --> 21:39.610
{\an1}<i>NINE OUT OF TEN RELIGIONS
FAIL IN THEIR FIRST YEAR.</i>

21:40.580 --> 21:42.110
{\an1}THAT'S GAME, HENDRIX.

21:43.280 --> 21:45.620
{\an1}GOD, I GOT TO ASK YOU
\h\h\h\h\h\hSOMETHING.

21:45.680 --> 21:47.520
{\an1}WHAT'S THE MEANING
\h\h\h\h\hOF LIFE?

21:47.590 --> 21:49.460
{\an1}<i>HOMER, I CAN'T TELL YOU THAT.</i>

21:49.520 --> 21:50.890
{\an1}COME ON.

21:50.960 --> 21:53.430
{\an1}<i>YOU'LL FIND OUT WHEN YOU DIE.</i>

21:53.490 --> 21:54.790
{\an1}I CAN'T WAIT.

21:54.860 --> 21:56.990
{\an1}<i>YOU CAN'T WAIT SIX MONTHS?</i>

21:57.060 --> 21:59.500
{\an1}\h\h\h\hHomer:
<i>NO, TELL ME NOW.</i>

21:59.560 --> 22:01.370
{\an1}\h\h\hGod:
<i>WELL, OKAY.</i>

22:01.430 --> 22:04.570
{\an1}<i>THE MEANING OF LIFE IS...</i>

22:07.040 --> 22:09.170
{\an1}\h\h\h\hCaptioned by VISUAL DATA
